I'll be just fine, Mr. Paley.
You know what a careful girl I am.

23
00:05:21,236 --> 00:05:24,260
我苦口婆心，你就是听不进去
I move my mouth, words come out,
you don't hear.

24
00:05:26,705 --> 00:05:31,105
- 我看电影要迟到了
- 我不喜欢你对着我笑
- I'm late for a movie.
- I don't like it when you smile at me.

25
00:05:31,306 --> 00:05:32,932
你不喜欢我笑吗？
You don't like my smile?

26
00:05:33,641 --> 00:05:35,505
我是不喜欢你笑里藏刀
I don't like what's behind it.

27
00:05:36,075 --> 00:05:40,567
听着，波莉，六个科学家失踪了
很可能已经死了
Listen, Polly, six scientists are missing,
probably dead.

28
00:05:40,777 --> 00:05:44,643
调查那件事情的人都很危险
我不想你也卷进去
Somebody out there means business.
I don't want you in the middle of it.

29
00:05:45,079 --> 00:05:48,013
仅仅只是去看一部电影，佩利先生
It's only a movie, Mr. Paley.

30
00:05:48,547 --> 00:05:49,946
我给你带些爆米花
I'll bring you some popcorn.

31
00:07:03,346 --> 00:07:06,836
图图，我感觉我们好像不在堪萨斯
Toto, I have a feeling
we're not in Kansas anymore.

32
00:07:07,048 --> 00:07:09,674
我们肯定在彩虹上
We must be over the rainbow.

33
00:07:14,784 --> 00:07:16,774
这是你寄给我的？
You sent me this?

34
00:07:18,853 --> 00:07:20,513
你是谁？
Who are you?

35
00:07:21,820 --> 00:07:24,686
- 这一切究竟是怎么回事
- 博士
- What's this all about, Mr...?
- Doctor.

36
00:07:24,923 --> 00:07:27,788
沃特・詹宁斯博士，我是一个化学家
Dr. Walter Jennings.
I'm a research chemist.

37
00:07:27,990 --> 00:07:30,286
我是研究核酸辐射的
I specialize in nucleic-acid emissions.

38
00:07:30,491 --> 00:07:32,583
就是蛋白质分子间的键...
The bonding enzymes
in proteus molecules which--

39
00:07:32,792 --> 00:07:35,385
那些失踪的科学家
你说你知道谁是下一个
The missing scientists.
You said you knew who was next.

40
00:07:36,894 --> 00:07:38,861
是的，我
Yes, l--

41
00:07:39,495 --> 00:07:41,189
我们见面的时间到了，博士
I have a deadline to meet, doctor.

42
00:07:42,729 --> 00:07:46,720
我是被选中的参加这个秘密试验的
七个科学家中的一个
I was one of seven scientists
chosen to serve in a secret facility

43
00:07:46,932 --> 00:07:50,991
在一战之前驻扎在柏林城外
stationed outside of Berlin
before the start of the First World War.

44
00:07:51,201 --> 00:07:55,726
它被称作Einheit Elf“11单元”
It was known only as Einheit Elf,
"Unit 1 1."

45
00:07:55,936 --> 00:07:59,301
我们发过誓，
永远不在实验室之外的地方谈论它
We agreed never to discuss
what went on behind those doors.

46
00:07:59,504 --> 00:08:02,562
在那里，我们所做的都是些
The things we were made
to do there...

47
00:08:02,805 --> 00:08:04,863
可怕的事情
Terrible things.

48
00:08:06,740 --> 00:08:10,265
- 我不该来的
- 现在我确信我们不在堪萨斯了
- I shouldn't have come.
- Now I know we're not in Kansas.

49
00:08:12,976 --> 00:08:14,966
你是一个好女巫还是一个坏女巫？
Are you a good witch
or a bad witch?

50
00:08:15,177 --> 00:08:17,041
博士，你说你知道谁是下一个
Doctor, you said you knew
who was next.

51
00:08:17,245 --> 00:08:18,939
是的
Yes.

52
00:08:19,745 --> 00:08:20,871
你没发现吗？
Don't you see?

53
00:08:21,246 --> 00:08:24,873
- 只剩下最后一个了
- 谁？他是谁，博士
- There is only one left.
- Who? Who is it, doctor?

54
00:08:25,248 --> 00:08:26,680
我
Me.

55
00:08:27,182 --> 00:08:29,581
他来抓我了
He's coming for me.

56
00:08:32,451 --> 00:08:34,543
谁？谁来了？
Who? Who's coming?

57
00:08:35,886 --> 00:08:37,045
托滕可夫
Totenkopf.

58
00:08:37,820 --> 00:08:39,446
托滕可夫
It's Totenkopf.

59
00:09:06,733 --> 00:09:08,256
瞧那
There!

60
00:09:11,935 --> 00:09:13,924
所有市民，请注意
All citizens, attention.

61
00:09:14,135 --> 00:09:17,035
纽约市必须马上疏散
New York City
must be evacuated at once.

62
00:09:17,238 --> 00:09:20,569
请大家有秩序撤到河东路
Proceed in an orderly manner
to the East River Drive.

63
00:09:20,772 --> 00:09:24,535
所有休息的警察和消防队员
All members of the police and fire
department on leave or off duty

64
00:09:24,740 --> 00:09:28,265
必须马上向上级报道
shall report immediately to their
precincts or company command.

65
00:09:28,475 --> 00:09:29,873
这很紧急
This is urgent.

66
00:09:37,646 --> 00:09:39,272
- 佩利编辑
- 佩利先生，是我，波莉
- Editor Paley.
- Mr. Paley, it's me, Polly.

67
00:09:39,480 --> 00:09:41,674
发生什么事了？他们要求撤离市中心
What's going on? They're calling
for midtown to evacuate.

68
00:09:41,881 --> 00:09:43,609
听着，佩利先生
我没有时间了
Listen, Mr. Paley,
I don't have much time.

69
00:09:43,815 --> 00:09:47,613
我要你搜集
所有关于沃特・詹宁斯博士的资料
I need you to dig up anything you can
on a Dr. Walter Jennings

70
00:09:47,817 --> 00:09:49,113
以及一个叫托滕可夫的人
and someone named Totenkopf.

71
00:09:49,317 --> 00:09:52,251
地址，电话号码，所有你可以找到的
这很重要
An address, a phone number,
anything you can find. It's important.

72
00:09:52,452 --> 00:09:54,316
托滕可夫是谁？
Totenkopf. Who is he?

73
00:09:54,519 --> 00:09:56,281
他可能与失踪的科学家有关
He may have something to do
with the missing scientists.

74
00:09:56,487 --> 00:09:58,147
尽快
Quick as you can.

75
00:09:58,355 --> 00:10:00,481
波莉 ，听我说
我要你离开这里
Polly, listen to me.
I want you to get out of there.

76
00:10:00,689 --> 00:10:02,781
我想你挂上电话，关上你的记事本
I want you to put the phone down,
close your notepad

77
00:10:02,990 --> 00:10:04,287
离开那个鬼地方
and get the hell out of there.

78
00:10:04,491 --> 00:10:06,117
等等
Wait a minute.

79
00:10:07,292 --> 00:10:11,226
我看见帕利赛饭店上空有一些东西
I can see something now coming
into sight above the Palisades.

80
00:10:11,827 --> 00:10:14,158
他们正在穿越第六大街
They're crossing Sixth Avenue.

81
00:10:14,795 --> 00:10:16,489
第五大街
Fifth Avenue.

82
00:10:16,696 --> 00:10:20,027
他们在一百码
他们在一百码之外
They're a hundred--
They're a hundred yards away.

83
00:10:20,265 --> 00:10:22,390
波莉，波莉！
Polly. Polly!

84
00:10:23,466 --> 00:10:25,126
天啊
Oh, my God.

85
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:26,629
波莉！
Polly!

86
00:10:26,834 --> 00:10:27,800
波莉！
Polly!

87
00:10:28,334 --> 00:10:29,800
波莉！
Polly!

88
00:10:33,536 --> 00:10:35,093
别跑！回来！
Stop! Come back!

89
00:11:10,686 --> 00:11:12,084
开火！
Fire!

90
00:11:21,724 --> 00:11:23,281
离开这儿！
Get out of here!

91
00:11:23,492 --> 00:11:26,220
他们已经突破了防线
要求支援
They've broken through the perimeter.
Send reinforcements.

92
00:11:26,426 --> 00:11:27,414
把你所有的部队都派来
Send everything you've got!

93
